I forgot to mention above that I have visited the wall, and found one inscription for a pararescue classmate, Charlie King, who should be one of our American heros, but is largely forgotten beyond the wall, and his buddies' memories.<br><br>
Maya, thank you for a memorial which includes the individual, and allows them to be continually remembered.<br><br>
Concerning racism, by boy taught me a great lesson, unknown to him, a few days ago when we were to play a chess game.  Playful jester that he is, he set up the game with each piece alternating color, so that each side had alternating white/black members.  I sat down to play, and said &quot;We can't play like this.  We won't know which side is whose!  It won't work.&quot;  Precisely!
